sequence.notes: A Buchwald-Hartwig C-S coupling reaction between 2,5-dimethylbenzenethiol and 1-bromo-2-methylbenzene (o-bromotoluene) to form a diaryl thioether.
Buchwald-Hartwig amination of an aryl bromide with piperazine to form vortioxetine.

The product structure shown in the screenshot is identical to the reactant structure. The reaction involves HBr at elevated temperature, which commonly implies the formation of the HBr salt (Vortioxetine hydrobromide). However, the drawn product structure is the free base, identical to the reactant. The SMILES has been corrected to reflect this structural identity after removing junk fragments and correcting the structural error in the provided product SMILES.
